cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with a problem in wireless networks, specifically in distributed opportunistic scheduling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a game theoretic approach to address the selfishness problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also mentions the use of control theory, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper conducts simulations, which could suggest it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia).
